The steps for connecting ESP32 to a webserver is:
1- set the esp32 chip to Soft Access Point Mode (AP).
2- setup the SID and password for the esp32 chip.
3- setup an arduino web server.
4- connect to the esp32 chip through the arduino web server by using the chip's ssid and password.
5- communicate with the esp32 chip through the arduino web server by using https requests.
